Coburg Peak (, ) is the rocky peak rising to 783 m in Erul Heights on Trinity Peninsula in Graham Land, Antarctica. It is surmounting Cugnot Ice Piedmont to the northeast.The peak is named after the Bulgarian royal house of Coburg (Saxe-Coburg-Gotha), 1887–1946. <S> [["Coburg Peak", "instance of", "Rocky peak"], ["Coburg Peak", "elevation", "783 m"], ["Coburg Peak", "location", "Erul Heights, Trinity Peninsula, Graham Land, Antarctica"], ["Coburg Peak", "surmounts", "Cugnot Ice Piedmont"], ["Coburg Peak", "named after", "Bulgarian royal house of Coburg (Saxe-Coburg-Gotha), 1887-1946"]]
Siniger Nunatak (, ‘Nunatak Siniger’ \'nu-na-tak si-'ni-ger\) is the rocky hill rising to over 500 m in the upper course of Russell East Glacier on Trinity Peninsula in Graham Land, Antarctica.The nunatak is named after the settlement of Siniger in Southern Bulgaria. <S> [["Siniger Nunatak", "instance of", "Rocky hill"], ["Siniger Nunatak", "height", "over 500 m"], ["Siniger Nunatak", "location", "Russell East Glacier"], ["Siniger Nunatak", "located in", "Trinity Peninsula"], ["Siniger Nunatak", "located in", "Graham Land"], ["Siniger Nunatak", "located in", "Antarctica"], ["Siniger Nunatak", "named after", "Siniger settlement"], ["Siniger settlement", "located in", "Southern Bulgaria"]]
Harald Kaas (19 May 1868 – 5 December 1953) was a Norwegian architect.Kaas was born in Christiania (now Oslo), Norway. He studied at the Norwegian National Academy of Craft and Art Industry, then at Baugewerkschule in Eckernförde and finally at Polytechnicum in Munich.He worked for a couple of years in the Colony of Natal in South Africa. He was employed by the Norwegian State Railways from 1908 to 1914, and designed stations on the Arendal Line, Bergen Line and Solør Line for the company. Kaas died on 5 December 1953 and was buried on 20 May 1954 at Vår Frelsers gravlund in Oslo. <S> [    ["Harald Kaas", "instance of", "Architect"],    ["Harald Kaas", "birth date", "19 May 1868"],    ["Harald Kaas", "death date", "5 December 1953"],    ["Harald Kaas", "place of birth", "Christiania"],    ["Harald Kaas", "studied at", "Norwegian National Academy of Craft and Art Industry"],    ["Harald Kaas", "studied at", "Baugewerkschule in Eckernförde"],    ["Harald Kaas", "studied at", "Polytechnicum in Munich"],    ["Harald Kaas", "worked in", "Colony of Natal in South Africa"],    ["Harald Kaas", "employer", "Norwegian State Railways"],    ["Harald Kaas", "designed stations on", "Arendal Line"],    ["Harald Kaas", "designed stations on", "Bergen Line"],    ["Harald Kaas", "designed stations on", "Solør Line"],    ["Harald Kaas", "burial date", "20 May 1954"],    ["Harald Kaas", "burial place", "Vår Frelsers gravlund in Oslo"]]
Utus Peak (, ) is the rocky peak rising to 1217 m in Trakiya Heights on Trinity Peninsula in Graham Land, Antarctica.The peak is named after the ancient Roman town of Utus in Northern Bulgaria. <S> [["Utus Peak", "instance of", "Rocky peak"], ["Utus Peak", "elevation", "1217 m"], ["Utus Peak", "location", "Trakiya Heights"], ["Trakiya Heights", "located on", "Trinity Peninsula"], ["Trinity Peninsula", "located in", "Graham Land"], ["Utus Peak", "named after", "Utus (town)"], ["Utus (town)", "located in", "Northern Bulgaria"]]
Everest Food Products Pvt Ltd (Everest Spices) is an Indian manufacturer, distributor and exporter of ground spices and spice mixtures under the brand name Everest.Everest has been accorded the Superbrands status three times: in 2003, 2006 and 2009. It also won FMCG Consumer Reaction Award. Everest started began advertising aggressively on the television in 2003, and by 2005, it had 30% share of the branded pure spices market in India. According to the 2007 study, Everest was India's largest spices brand based in Mumbai. More than 2 crore (20 million) households used Everest spices regularly. The brand was stocked by 4 Lakh (4,00,000) outlets in more than 1,000 towns across India. More than 370 crore (3.705 billion) packs of Everest product were sold each year. There were more than 42 blends under the Everest brand name.Everest also exports its products to US, Middle East, Singapore, Australia, New Zealand, East Africa and other countries.Everest Spices, being one of the leading players, aggressively competes with MDH, which has 12% market share. <S> [    ["Everest Food Products Pvt Ltd", "type", "Manufacturer"],    ["Everest Food Products Pvt Ltd", "type", "Distributor"],    ["Everest Food Products Pvt Ltd", "type", "Exporter"],    ["Everest Food Products Pvt Ltd", "country", "India"],    ["Everest Food Products Pvt Ltd", "brand name", "Everest"],    ["Everest Food Products Pvt Ltd", "awards", "Superbrands status (2003)"],    ["Everest Food Products Pvt Ltd", "awards", "Superbrands status (2006)"],    ["Everest Food Products Pvt Ltd", "awards", "Superbrands status (2009)"],    ["Everest Food Products Pvt Ltd", "awards", "FMCG Consumer Reaction Award"],    ["Everest Food Products Pvt Ltd", "market share", "30% (2005)"],    ["Everest Food Products Pvt Ltd", "headquarters", "Mumbai"],    ["Everest Food Products Pvt Ltd", "households using products", "20 million"],    ["Everest Food Products Pvt Ltd", "outlets stocking products", "400,000"],    ["Everest Food Products Pvt Ltd", "packs sold per year", "3.705 billion"],    ["Everest Food Products Pvt Ltd", "blends under brand name", "42"],    ["Everest Food Products Pvt Ltd", "export destinations", ["US", "Middle East", "Singapore", "Australia", "New Zealand", "East Africa"]],    ["Everest Food Products Pvt Ltd", "competitor", "MDH"],    ["MDH", "market share", "12%"]]
Jallo Park (sometimes called Jallo Wildlife Park), established in 1978, is a public recreation and wildlife site located in Lahore District, Punjab, Pakistan. Spread over an area of , it is one of the three main wildlife parks located in Lahore, the other two being Changa Manga and Lahore Zoo Safari. The park is east to Lahore city. Facilities at Jallo Park include a Forest Research Centre, Wildlife Breeding Center, restaurants, coffee shops, a theme park, a sports complex, swimming pool, and a large lake for fishing and boating. It is currently funded by Punjab Wildlife and Parks Department of Government of Punjab. It is easily accessible by taxi, TransLahore buses and Lahore City Commuter trains that stop at Jallo Railway Station.Now the Botanical Garden Jallo is the part of this biggest Wildlife park Jallo. <S> [    ["Jallo Park", "instance of", "Public recreation and wildlife site"],    ["Jallo Park", "established", "1978"],    ["Jallo Park", "located in", "Lahore District, Punjab, Pakistan"],    ["Jallo Park", "size", "area"],    ["Jallo Park", "part of", "Lahore"],    ["Jallo Park", "facilities include", "Forest Research Centre"],    ["Jallo Park", "facilities include", "Wildlife Breeding Center"],    ["Jallo Park", "facilities include", "restaurants"],    ["Jallo Park", "facilities include", "coffee shops"],    ["Jallo Park", "facilities include", "theme park"],    ["Jallo Park", "facilities include", "sports complex"],    ["Jallo Park", "facilities include", "swimming pool"],    ["Jallo Park", "facilities include", "large lake for fishing and boating"],    ["Jallo Park", "funded by", "Punjab Wildlife and Parks Department of Government of Punjab"],    ["Jallo Park", "accessible by", "taxi"],    ["Jallo Park", "accessible by", "TransLahore buses"],    ["Jallo Park", "accessible by", "Lahore City Commuter trains"],    ["Jallo Park", "stop at", "Jallo Railway Station"],    ["Jallo Park", "includes", "Botanical Garden Jallo"]]
Paul L. Foster is an American businessman who is chairman of the board of Western Refining, a Fortune 200 and Global 2000 oil refiner and marketer based in El Paso, Texas. <S> [["Paul L. Foster", "nationality", "American"], ["Paul L. Foster", "occupation", "Businessman"], ["Paul L. Foster", "position", "Chairman of the board"], ["Paul L. Foster", "company", "Western Refining"], ["Western Refining", "industry", "Oil refining and marketing"], ["Western Refining", "fortune ranking", "200"], ["Western Refining", "global ranking", "2000"], ["Western Refining", "location", "El Paso, Texas"]]
Júlia Hajdú (8 September 1915 – 23 October 1987) was a Hungarian composer and pianist. She was born into a Jewish family in Budapest, and died in the same city. <S> [["Júlia Hajdú", "instance of", "Composer"], ["Júlia Hajdú", "instance of", "Pianist"], ["Júlia Hajdú", "birth date", "8 September 1915"], ["Júlia Hajdú", "death date", "23 October 1987"], ["Júlia Hajdú", "ethnicity", "Jewish"], ["Júlia Hajdú", "place of birth", "Budapest"], ["Júlia Hajdú", "place of death", "Budapest"]]
The American Repertory Ballet (ARB) is an American ballet company based in New Jersey.The company was founded by Audrée Estey in 1963, as the Princeton Regional Ballet Company. In 1978, it became a professional company and was renamed Princeton Ballet Company. It was named American Repertory Ballet in 1990. The former Garden State Ballet merged with ARB during the 1995-1996 season.ARB is a founding resident company of the New Brunswick Performing Arts Center. <S> [["American Repertory Ballet", "instance of", "Ballet company"], ["American Repertory Ballet", "based in", "New Jersey"], ["American Repertory Ballet", "founded by", "Audrée Estey"], ["American Repertory Ballet", "founded in", "1963"], ["American Repertory Ballet", "former name", "Princeton Regional Ballet Company"], ["American Repertory Ballet", "renamed to", "Princeton Ballet Company"], ["American Repertory Ballet", "renamed to", "American Repertory Ballet"], ["Garden State Ballet", "merged with", "American Repertory Ballet"], ["American Repertory Ballet", "resident company of", "New Brunswick Performing Arts Center"]]
L'Oisans is a region in the French Alps, located in the départements of l'Isère and Hautes-Alpes, and corresponding to the drainage basin of the River Romanche and its tributaries (Eau d'Olle, Lignarre, Sarenne, Vénéon and Ferrand). Between Livet-et-Gavet and Le Bourg-d'Oisans, the Romanche forms a deep gorge.Its geographical definition coincides almost exactly with the former cantons of Le Bourg-d'Oisans (Isère) and La Grave (Hautes Alpes).The Oisans covers parts of the massifs of Belledonne, Taillefer, Grandes Rousses, Arves and Écrins.The highest point in the region is the mountain of "Pic Lory", a subpeak of the Barre des Écrins which reaches a height of 4,088 metres, but the most symbolic peak is la Meije which is nicknamed the "Queen of the Oisans".The Oisans is a remarkable territory, thanks to its numerous mountain chains, valleys, rivers, streams and plains.The Oisans is a very touristic region, both for winter and summer sports. Oisans regularly hosts the Tour de France as well as many major sporting events on a European scale (Super-Biker, World of Snowboarding, Skiing World, the Bike Festival, Andros Trophy or the Criterium Cyclist of Dauphiné Libéré).The provincial road 1091 (formerly RN 91) is the main access road into this area, beginning in the town of Livet-et-Gavet. In recent years, the RD1091 has been significantly upgraded, with various ring roads that provide faster access and more enjoyable access to the Oisans.The town of Bourg d'Oisans is the equivalent of the capital of this territory because this town is at the centre of six valleys.The main towns are Bourg d'Oisans, Les Deux Alpes, Livet-et-Gavet and Huez. <S> [    ["L'Oisans", "located in", "French Alps"],    ["L'Oisans", "departments", ["l'Isère", "Hautes-Alpes"]],    ["L'Oisans", "drainage basin", ["River Romanche", "Eau d'Olle", "Lignarre", "Sarenne", "Vénéon", "Ferrand"]],    ["Romanche", "forms", "deep gorge"],    ["Oisans", "covers parts of", ["massifs of Belledonne", "Taillefer", "Grandes Rousses", "Arves", "Écrins"]],    ["Oisans", "highest point", "mountain of Pic Lory"],    ["Pic Lory", "subpeak of", "Barre des Écrins"],    ["Oisans", "symbolic peak", "la Meije"],    ["la Meije", "nicknamed", "Queen of the Oisans"],    ["Oisans", "remarkable territory", "numerous mountain chains, valleys, rivers, streams, plains"],    ["Oisans", "touristic region for", ["winter sports", "summer sports"]],    ["Oisans", "hosts", ["Tour de France", "major sporting events"]],    ["Oisans", "access road", "provincial road 1091"],    ["provincial road 1091", "begins in", "Livet-et-Gavet"],    ["Bourg d'Oisans", "capital of", "Oisans"],    ["Bourg d'Oisans", "located in", "six valleys"],    ["Main towns", ["Bourg d'Oisans", "Les Deux Alpes", "Livet-et-Gavet", "Huez"]]]
The Voca People () is an Israel-based ensemble performing vocal theater combining a cappella and beat box vocals to reproduce the sounds of an entire orchestra.They have performed in Spain, The USA, Hungary, Italy, France, England, Israel and many other places. They incorporate the public into their songs and change or add bits depending on which country they are in (e.g. If they were in Spain they would perform songs in Spanish and incorporate the Spanish public into their performance.) <S> [["The Voca People", "instance of", "Ensemble"], ["The Voca People", "based in", "Israel"], ["The Voca People", "performance style", "Vocal theater"], ["The Voca People", "incorporates", "A cappella vocals"], ["The Voca People", "incorporates", "Beat box vocals"], ["The Voca People", "performed in", "Spain"], ["The Voca People", "performed in", "USA"], ["The Voca People", "performed in", "Hungary"], ["The Voca People", "performed in", "Italy"], ["The Voca People", "performed in", "France"], ["The Voca People", "performed in", "England"], ["The Voca People", "performed in", "Israel"], ["The Voca People", "incorporates", "Public into songs"], ["The Voca People", "changes/adds", "Bits depending on country"], ["The Voca People", "performs songs in", "Spanish"], ["The Voca People", "incorporates", "Spanish public into performance"]]
Pseudopostega cretea is a moth of the family Opostegidae. It was described by Edward Meyrick in 1920. It is known from the eastern half of North America from southern Canada (including Ontario) south to northern Florida, west to south-eastern British Columbia and Texas.The length of the forewings is 3.9–4.6 mm. Adults have been recorded from May to July (with one early August record) in the southern United States and from June to August across the northern part of its broad range. <S> [["Pseudopostega cretea", "instance of", "Moth"], ["Pseudopostega cretea", "family", "Opostegidae"], ["Pseudopostega cretea", "described by", "Edward Meyrick"], ["Pseudopostega cretea", "length of forewings", "3.9-4.6 mm"], ["Pseudopostega cretea", "location", "North America"], ["Pseudopostega cretea", "region", "eastern half"], ["Pseudopostega cretea", "known from", "southern Canada"], ["Pseudopostega cretea", "known from", "Ontario"], ["Pseudopostega cretea", "known from", "northern Florida"], ["Pseudopostega cretea", "known from", "south-eastern British Columbia"], ["Pseudopostega cretea", "known from", "Texas"], ["Pseudopostega cretea", "recorded from", "May to July"], ["Pseudopostega cretea", "recorded from", "June to August"], ["Pseudopostega cretea", "recorded from", "southern United States"], ["Pseudopostega cretea", "recorded from", "northern part"], ["Pseudopostega cretea", "recorded from", "broad range"]]
