Eros Vlahos (born 13 January 1995) is an English-Greek actor and comedian, probably best known for his roles as Cyril Gray in "Nanny McPhee and the Big Bang", Jake Farley in "Summer in Transylvania", and Lommy Greenhands in "Game of Thrones". He also appeared in a recurring role on the television series "Da Vinci's Demons", as Nico Machiavelli. <S> [["Eros Vlahos", "instance of", "Actor"], ["Eros Vlahos", "nationality", "English-Greek"], ["Eros Vlahos", "date of birth", "13 January 1995"], ["Eros Vlahos", "known for", "Cyril Gray in Nanny McPhee and the Big Bang"], ["Eros Vlahos", "known for", "Jake Farley in Summer in Transylvania"], ["Eros Vlahos", "known for", "Lommy Greenhands in Game of Thrones"], ["Eros Vlahos", "appeared in", "Da Vinci's Demons as Nico Machiavelli"]]
