Do Dooni Chaar () is a 2010 Indian Hindi family comedy-drama film produced by Arindam Chaudhuri (Planman Motion Pictures), written and directed by debutant director Habib Faisal, and starring Rishi Kapoor, Neetu Singh, Aditi Vasudev and Archit Krishna in lead roles. The film is about a middle-class school teacher who tries to keep his wife and children happy in inflationary times and dreams of buying a car. The movie also marks the return of the Kapoor pair as a lead couple on the silver screen. Although the duo had not acted in a film in over 30 years, they had previously acted in numerous hits during the 1970s. The directorial debut film was also the first live-action Hindi film to be distributed by Disney World Cinema. It went on to win the National Film Award for Best Feature Film in Hindi at the 58th National Film Awards. <S> [["Do Dooni Chaar", "instance of", "Indian Hindi family comedy-drama film"], ["Do Dooni Chaar", "producer", "Arindam Chaudhuri (Planman Motion Pictures)"], ["Do Dooni Chaar", "writer", "Habib Faisal"], ["Do Dooni Chaar", "director", "Habib Faisal"], ["Do Dooni Chaar", "starring", "Rishi Kapoor, Neetu Singh, Aditi Vasudev, Archit Krishna"], ["Do Dooni Chaar", "plot", "middle-class school teacher trying to keep family happy in inflationary times and dreaming of buying a car"], ["Do Dooni Chaar", "distribution", "Disney World Cinema"], ["Do Dooni Chaar", "awards", "National Film Award for Best Feature Film in Hindi at the 58th National Film Awards"]]
Brakšķi Station is a railway station on the Tukums II – Jelgava Railway. <S> [["Brakšķi Station", "instance of", "Railway station"], ["Brakšķi Station", "located on", "Tukums II - Jelgava Railway"]]
Södermanland Runic Inscription 352 or Sö 352 is a Viking Age memorial runestone located at Linga, which is about two kilometers south of Järna, Stockholm County, Sweden, which was in the historic province of Södermanland. The inscription depicts a ship with an anchor and a portion of the runic text uses same-stave bind runes on the ship mast. <S> [["Södermanland Runic Inscription 352", "instance of", "Viking Age memorial runestone"], ["Södermanland Runic Inscription 352", "location", "Linga"], ["Södermanland Runic Inscription 352", "distance from", "Järna, Stockholm County, Sweden"], ["Södermanland Runic Inscription 352", "historic province", "Södermanland"], ["Södermanland Runic Inscription 352", "depicts", "ship with anchor"], ["Södermanland Runic Inscription 352", "uses", "same-stave bind runes on ship mast"]]
Emblemaria biocellata, the Twospot blenny, is a species of chaenopsid blenny found in coral reefs around Venezuela, French Guiana, and Colombia, in the western Atlantic Ocean. Males of this species can reach a maximum length of TL, while females can reach a maximum length of SL. <S> [["Emblemaria biocellata", "instance of", "Species"], ["Emblemaria biocellata", "common name", "Twospot blenny"], ["Emblemaria biocellata", "habitat", "Coral reefs"], ["Emblemaria biocellata", "location", "Venezuela"], ["Emblemaria biocellata", "location", "French Guiana"], ["Emblemaria biocellata", "location", "Colombia"], ["Emblemaria biocellata", "ocean", "Western Atlantic Ocean"], ["Emblemaria biocellata", "maximum length", "TL (males)"], ["Emblemaria biocellata", "maximum length", "SL (females)"]]
Juraj Dančík (born 21 February 1982) is a Slovak former football player. <S> [["Juraj Dančík", "instance of", "Football player"], ["Juraj Dančík", "country of origin", "Slovakia"], ["Juraj Dančík", "date of birth", "21 February 1982"], ["Juraj Dančík", "current status", "former"]]
The 2010–11 Basketball League of Serbia season was the 5th season of the Basketball League of Serbia, the highest professional basketball league in Serbia. It was also 67th national championship played by Serbian clubs inclusive of nation's previous incarnations as Yugoslavia and Serbia & Montenegro.The 182-game regular season (26 games for each of the 14 teams) began on Saturday, October 9, 2010, and ended on Sunday, March 12, 2011. <S> [["2010-11 Basketball League of Serbia season", "instance of", "Basketball League season"], ["2010-11 Basketball League of Serbia season", "season number", "5"], ["2010-11 Basketball League of Serbia season", "country", "Serbia"], ["2010-11 Basketball League of Serbia season", "professional league", "Basketball League of Serbia"], ["2010-11 Basketball League of Serbia season", "national championship number", "67"], ["2010-11 Basketball League of Serbia season", "regular season games", "182"], ["2010-11 Basketball League of Serbia season", "start date", "October 9, 2010"], ["2010-11 Basketball League of Serbia season", "end date", "March 12, 2011"]]
