Pierre Adamoli (5 August 1707 – 3 June 1769) was an 18th-century French collector. He is remembered as a great bibliophile of the Age of Enlightenment. <S> [["Pierre Adamoli", "instance of", "Collector"], ["Pierre Adamoli", "birth date", "5 August 1707"], ["Pierre Adamoli", "death date", "3 June 1769"], ["Pierre Adamoli", "nationality", "French"], ["Pierre Adamoli", "remembered for", "Great bibliophile of the Age of Enlightenment"]]
Owl Peak () is in the northern Teton Range, Grand Teton National Park, Wyoming and is just east of Elk Mountain. The peak is located west of and across Jackson Lake from Lizard Creek Campground. Access to the peak is easiest by boat to the Berry Creek Trailhead at Wilcox Point then heading west at the Owl Creek Trail. After a hike along Berry Creek and Owl Creek trails, off trail access to the summit can be achieved after a steep ascent of an additional . North of the mountain, the Tetons blend into the Yellowstone Plateau while to the south lies Webb Canyon. <S> [["Owl Peak", "located in", "Teton Range"], ["Owl Peak", "located in", "Grand Teton National Park"], ["Owl Peak", "located in", "Wyoming"], ["Owl Peak", "east of", "Elk Mountain"], ["Owl Peak", "west of", "Jackson Lake"], ["Owl Peak", "across from", "Lizard Creek Campground"], ["Access to Owl Peak", "easiest by", "boat to Berry Creek Trailhead"], ["Berry Creek Trailhead", "located at", "Wilcox Point"], ["Wilcox Point", "direction", "west"], ["Berry Creek Trail", "leads to", "Owl Creek Trail"], ["Owl Creek Trail", "leads to", "summit"], ["Summit of Owl Peak", "accessed by", "steep ascent"], ["Tetons", "north of", "Yellowstone Plateau"], ["Tetons", "south of", "Webb Canyon"]]
Azamn is an independent Arabic newspaper in the Sultanate of Oman on the Arabian peninsula. It was suspended by the Omani government on August 9, 2016 following a report about senior Omani officials pressuring the country's judiciary to overturn a decision in an inheritance case. On September 26, a court ordered its permanent closure. <S> [["Azamn", "instance of", "Newspaper"], ["Azamn", "language", "Arabic"], ["Azamn", "location", "Sultanate of Oman"], ["Sultanate of Oman", "located in", "Arabian Peninsula"], ["Azamn", "suspended by", "Omani government"], ["Omani government", "date of suspension", "August 9, 2016"], ["Omani government", "reason for suspension", "report about senior Omani officials pressuring country's judiciary"], ["Omani government", "action taken", "suspended Azamn"], ["Court", "ordered", "permanent closure of Azamn"], ["Date of court order", "September 26, 2016"]]
