Gerze Tunnel (), is a highway tunnel constructed in Sinop Province, northern Turkey.Gerze Tunnel is part of the Sinop-Samsun Highway within the Black Sea Coastal Highway, of which construction was carried out by the Turkish Cengiz Construction Company. The -long twin-tube tunnel carrying two lanes of traffic in each direction is flanked by -long Demirciköy Tunnel in the northwest and -long Yenikent Tunnel in the southeast on the same highway.The tunnel was opened to traffic on 26 March 2014. <S> [["Gerze Tunnel", "instance of", "Highway tunnel"], ["Gerze Tunnel", "location", "Sinop Province, Turkey"], ["Gerze Tunnel", "part of", "Sinop-Samsun Highway"], ["Sinop-Samsun Highway", "part of", "Black Sea Coastal Highway"], ["Sinop-Samsun Highway", "constructed by", "Turkish Cengiz Construction Company"], ["Gerze Tunnel", "length", "-long"], ["Gerze Tunnel", "lanes", "2"], ["Demirciköy Tunnel", "length", "-long"], ["Yenikent Tunnel", "length", "-long"], ["Gerze Tunnel", "opened to traffic on", "26 March 2014"]]
