Robin Koch (; born 17 July 1996) is a German professional footballer who plays as a defender for Premier League club Leeds United and the German national team.Koch has previously played for Eintracht Trier II, Eintracht Trier, 1. FC Kaiserslautern II, 1. FC Kaiserslautern and SC Freiburg, and also represented Germany at under-21 level. In August 2020, he signed for Leeds United ahead of their Premier League return. <S> [["Robin Koch", "birth date", "17 July 1996"], ["Robin Koch", "nationality", "German"], ["Robin Koch", "occupation", "professional footballer"], ["Robin Koch", "position", "defender"], ["Robin Koch", "current club", "Leeds United"], ["Robin Koch", "previous clubs", "Eintracht Trier II, Eintracht Trier, 1. FC Kaiserslautern II, 1. FC Kaiserslautern, SC Freiburg"], ["Robin Koch", "national team", "Germany"], ["Robin Koch", "youth team", "Germany under-21"], ["Leeds United", "signed player", "Robin Koch"], ["Leeds United", "league", "Premier League"], ["Leeds United", "return to league", "August 2020"]]
