Monopoly Streets is a video game based on the board game of the same name, and one of many in the Monopoly video game series. Developed by EA Salt Lake and published by Electronic Arts, the game was released on the PlayStation 3, Xbox 360, and Wii on October 26, 2010. <S> [["Monopoly Streets", "instance of", "Video game"], ["Monopoly Streets", "based on", "Monopoly board game"], ["Monopoly Streets", "part of", "Monopoly video game series"], ["Monopoly Streets", "developed by", "EA Salt Lake"], ["Monopoly Streets", "published by", "Electronic Arts"], ["Monopoly Streets", "released on", "PlayStation 3"], ["Monopoly Streets", "released on", "Xbox 360"], ["Monopoly Streets", "released on", "Wii"], ["Monopoly Streets", "release date", "October 26, 2010"]]
Re Daniel Dawal Migel 3 () is a 2004 Sri Lankan Sinhala comedy, action film directed by Roy de Silva and produced by Soma Edirisinghe for E.A.P Films. It is the third and final film of Re Daniel Dawal Migel film franchise and sequel to 2000 "Re Daniel Dawal Migel 2" film. The comic duo Bandu Samarasinghe, and Tennyson Cooray reprised lead roles along with Dilhani Ekanayake, Jayantha Bopearachchi and Sanoja Bibile. Music for the film is done by Somapala Rathnayake. The film also became one of Sri Lanka's blockbuster hit in cinema theatres, but failure when comparing first two installments. It is the 1031st Sri Lankan film in the Sinhala cinema. <S> [["Re Daniel Dawal Migel 3", "instance of", "Film"], ["Re Daniel Dawal Migel 3", "country", "Sri Lanka"], ["Re Daniel Dawal Migel 3", "genre", "Comedy"], ["Re Daniel Dawal Migel 3", "genre", "Action"], ["Re Daniel Dawal Migel 3", "director", "Roy de Silva"], ["Re Daniel Dawal Migel 3", "producer", "Soma Edirisinghe"], ["Re Daniel Dawal Migel 3", "production company", "E.A.P Films"], ["Re Daniel Dawal Migel 3", "sequel to", "Re Daniel Dawal Migel 2"], ["Re Daniel Dawal Migel 3", "cast", "Bandu Samarasinghe"], ["Re Daniel Dawal Migel 3", "cast", "Tennyson Cooray"], ["Re Daniel Dawal Migel 3", "cast", "Dilhani Ekanayake"], ["Re Daniel Dawal Migel 3", "cast", "Jayantha Bopearachchi"], ["Re Daniel Dawal Migel 3", "cast", "Sanoja Bibile"], ["Re Daniel Dawal Migel 3", "music by", "Somapala Rathnayake"], ["Re Daniel Dawal Migel 3", "box office performance", "Blockbuster hit"], ["Re Daniel Dawal Migel 3", "box office performance", "Failure compared to first two installments"], ["Re Daniel Dawal Migel 3", "Sri Lankan film number", "1031st"]]
