Revaz Nadareishvili (born June 21, 1991) is a Georgian Greco-Roman wrestler. He won a bronze medal at the 2017 World Wrestling Championships. He competed in the men's Greco-Roman 98 kg event at the 2016 Summer Olympics, in which he was eliminated in the round of 16 by Elis Guri. <S> [["Revaz Nadareishvili", "instance of", "Greco-Roman wrestler"], ["Revaz Nadareishvili", "country", "Georgia"], ["Revaz Nadareishvili", "birth date", "June 21, 1991"], ["Revaz Nadareishvili", "medal", "bronze"], ["Revaz Nadareishvili", "event", "2017 World Wrestling Championships"], ["Revaz Nadareishvili", "event", "2016 Summer Olympics"], ["Revaz Nadareishvili", "eliminated by", "Elis Guri"], ["Elis Guri", "instance of", "Greco-Roman wrestler"], ["Elis Guri", "event", "2016 Summer Olympics"], ["Elis Guri", "round", "16"]]
