Crack'ed, subtitled "An Egg-Citing Adventure," is a target shooting video game developed by Robert Craig (credited as Robert Neve) for the Atari ST and released by Atari Corporation in 1988. An Atari 7800 port was published the same year. In "Crack'ed" the player must protect bird eggs by shooting predators.An Atari 2600 version was in development, but never released. <S> [    ["Crack'ed", "subtitle", "An Egg-Citing Adventure"],    ["Crack'ed", "genre", "Target shooting video game"],    ["Crack'ed", "developer", "Robert Craig"],    ["Crack'ed", "credited as", "Robert Neve"],    ["Crack'ed", "platform", "Atari ST"],    ["Crack'ed", "released by", "Atari Corporation"],    ["Crack'ed", "release year", 1988],    ["Crack'ed", "port", "Atari 7800"],    ["Crack'ed", "published", "same year"],    ["Crack'ed", "objective", "protect bird eggs by shooting predators"],    ["Atari 2600 version", "status", "in development"],    ["Atari 2600 version", "released", "never"]]
