Kuanysh Rymkulov also written as Qwanış Rımqulov (Куаныш Рымкулов or Қуаныш Рымқұлов, born ) is a Kazakhstani male weightlifter, competing in the 85 kg category and representing Kazakhstan at international competitions. He participated at the 1996 Summer Olympics in the 83 kg event. He competed at world championships, most recently at the 1999 World Weightlifting Championships. <S> [["Kuanysh Rymkulov", "also written as", "Qwanış Rımqulov"], ["Kuanysh Rymkulov", "country", "Kazakhstan"], ["Kuanysh Rymkulov", "gender", "male"], ["Kuanysh Rymkulov", "sport", "weightlifting"], ["Kuanysh Rymkulov", "weight category", "85 kg"], ["Kuanysh Rymkulov", "represented by", "Kazakhstan"], ["Kuanysh Rymkulov", "event", "1996 Summer Olympics - 83 kg"], ["Kuanysh Rymkulov", "participated in", "world championships"], ["Kuanysh Rymkulov", "most recent participation", "1999 World Weightlifting Championships"]]
"Basket of deplorables" is a phrase from a 2016 presidential election campaign speech delivered by Democratic nominee Hillary Clinton on September 9, 2016, at a campaign fundraising event, which she used to describe half of the supporters of her opponent, Republican nominee Donald Trump saying "They're racist, sexist, homophobic, xenophobic". The next day, she expressed regret for "saying half", while insisting that Trump had deplorably amplified "hateful views and voices".The Trump campaign repeatedly used the phrase against Clinton during and after the 2016 presidential election. Many Trump supporters adopted the "deplorable" moniker for themselves in reappropriation. Some journalists and political analysts questioned whether this incident played a role in the election's outcome. Clinton admitted in her 2017 book "What Happened" that it was one of the factors for her loss. <S> [    ["Basket of deplorables", "phrase from", "2016 presidential election campaign speech"],    ["Basket of deplorables", "delivered by", "Hillary Clinton"],    ["Basket of deplorables", "date", "September 9, 2016"],    ["Basket of deplorables", "event", "campaign fundraising event"],    ["Basket of deplorables", "description", "used to describe half of the supporters of Donald Trump"],    ["Hillary Clinton", "nominee of", "Democratic party"],    ["Donald Trump", "nominee of", "Republican party"],    ["Hillary Clinton", "expressed regret for", "saying half"],    ["Donald Trump", "used the phrase against", "Clinton"],    ["Trump supporters", "adopted", "deplorable moniker"],    ["Journalists", "questioned", "role in election outcome"],    ["Hillary Clinton", "admitted in", "2017 book 'What Happened'"],    ["2016 presidential election campaign speech", "played a role in", "election outcome"]]
