Zhao Jingyi (趙敬怡) (died March 24, 929) was a general of the Chinese Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms Period state Later Tang, serving as one of emperor's chiefs of staff ("Shumishi") from 928 to 929. Prior to serving as chief of staff, he was the deputy military governor of Tianxiong Circuit (天雄, headquartered in modern Handan, Hebei). He died in office as "Shumishi". As there was no biography for him in the "Old History of the Five Dynasties" or the "New History of the Five Dynasties", there is otherwise no extant record of his career. <S> [["Zhao Jingyi", "instance of", "General"], ["Zhao Jingyi", "country", "China"], ["Zhao Jingyi", "period", "Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms Period"], ["Zhao Jingyi", "state", "Later Tang"], ["Zhao Jingyi", "title", "Chief of staff"], ["Zhao Jingyi", "title", "Deputy military governor"], ["Zhao Jingyi", "location", "Tianxiong Circuit"], ["Tianxiong Circuit", "headquartered in", "Handan, Hebei"], ["Zhao Jingyi", "date of death", "March 24, 929"], ["Zhao Jingyi", "cause of death", "In office as Chief of staff"], ["Zhao Jingyi", "biography", "Not available in Old History of the Five Dynasties"], ["Zhao Jingyi", "biography", "Not available in New History of the Five Dynasties"]]
Krzysztof Bartnicki (born 1971) is a Polish translator, writer, musician/composer, lexicographer and Joyce scholar. His translations into English include poetry of Stanisław Dróżdż and Bolesław Leśmian. He is the author of several Polish-English dictionaries. <S> [["Krzysztof Bartnicki", "occupation", "Translator"], ["Krzysztof Bartnicki", "occupation", "Writer"], ["Krzysztof Bartnicki", "occupation", "Musician/Composer"], ["Krzysztof Bartnicki", "occupation", "Lexicographer"], ["Krzysztof Bartnicki", "occupation", "Joyce Scholar"], ["Krzysztof Bartnicki", "birth year", 1971], ["Krzysztof Bartnicki", "nationality", "Polish"], ["Krzysztof Bartnicki", "translations into", "English"], ["Krzysztof Bartnicki", "translations of", "Stanisław Dróżdż poetry"], ["Krzysztof Bartnicki", "translations of", "Bolesław Leśmian poetry"], ["Krzysztof Bartnicki", "author of", "Polish-English dictionaries"]]
Bedopassa Buassat (born September 20, 1992) is a Bissau-Guinean freestyle wrestler. He competed in the men's freestyle 97 kg event at the 2016 Summer Olympics, in which he was eliminated in the round of 32 by Magomed Ibragimov. <S> [["Bedopassa Buassat", "instance of", "Freestyle wrestler"], ["Bedopassa Buassat", "nationality", "Bissau-Guinean"], ["Bedopassa Buassat", "event", "Men's freestyle 97 kg at 2016 Summer Olympics"], ["Bedopassa Buassat", "eliminated by", "Magomed Ibragimov"]]
The 2017 Milwaukee Brewers season was the 48th season for the Brewers in Milwaukee, the 20th in the National League, and 49th overall. The Brewers were managed by Craig Counsell in his third season as manager. They finished the season 86–76 to finish six games behind the Chicago Cubs in the National League Central Division. The Brewers finished one game behind the Colorado Rockies for the second Wild Card spot. The season marked the first time the Brewers had finished above .500 in three years and their best season in terms of winning percentage since 2011. <S> [["2017 Milwaukee Brewers season", "season number", "48th"], ["2017 Milwaukee Brewers season", "team", "Milwaukee Brewers"], ["2017 Milwaukee Brewers season", "league", "National League"], ["2017 Milwaukee Brewers season", "overall season number", "49th"], ["2017 Milwaukee Brewers season", "manager", "Craig Counsell"], ["2017 Milwaukee Brewers season", "manager season number", "third"], ["2017 Milwaukee Brewers season", "season record", "86-76"], ["2017 Milwaukee Brewers season", "games behind", "6"], ["2017 Milwaukee Brewers season", "division", "National League Central Division"], ["2017 Milwaukee Brewers season", "Wild Card spot", "second"], ["2017 Milwaukee Brewers season", "above .500 finish years", "3"], ["2017 Milwaukee Brewers season", "best season winning percentage", "2011"]]
The 2017 St. Louis Cardinals season was the 136th for the St. Louis Cardinals of Major League Baseball (MLB), a franchise in St. Louis, Missouri. It was the 126th season for the Cardinals in the National League (NL), and their 12th at Busch Stadium III. The Cardinals missed the playoffs for a second consecutive season, having last done that between the 2007 and 2008 seasons. <S> [["2017 St. Louis Cardinals season", "instance of", "Sports season"], ["2017 St. Louis Cardinals season", "team", "St. Louis Cardinals"], ["2017 St. Louis Cardinals season", "league", "Major League Baseball"], ["2017 St. Louis Cardinals season", "franchise location", "St. Louis, Missouri"], ["2017 St. Louis Cardinals season", "stadium", "Busch Stadium III"], ["2017 St. Louis Cardinals season", "playoff status", "missed playoffs"], ["2017 St. Louis Cardinals season", "consecutive seasons", "2"], ["2017 St. Louis Cardinals season", "previous playoff miss", "2007-2008 seasons"]]
