Sonia Shirsat is a Fado singer from Ponda taluka, Goa, India. She has been referred to as "the ambassador of Goan music to the world" and has performed across India and the world and often during cultural and music events in Goa. She sings in 13 different languages Shirsat, as of 2019, has been promoting the Fado in Goa, by holding training and introductory classes to this form of music at various parts of the region. <S> [["Sonia Shirsat", "occupation", "Fado singer"], ["Sonia Shirsat", "from", "Ponda taluka, Goa, India"], ["Sonia Shirsat", "nickname", "the ambassador of Goan music to the world"], ["Sonia Shirsat", "activities", "performing across India and the world"], ["Sonia Shirsat", "activities", "performing during cultural and music events in Goa"], ["Sonia Shirsat", "languages", "13"], ["Sonia Shirsat", "promoting", "Fado in Goa"], ["Sonia Shirsat", "activities", "holding training and introductory classes to Fado in various parts of the region"]]
The 1952 West Riding County Council election was held on Saturday, 5 April 1952. The election took place in the administrative county of the West Riding of Yorkshire, which excluded the county boroughs of Barnsley, Bradford, Dewsbury, Doncaster, Halifax, Huddersfield, Leeds, Rotherham, Sheffield, Wakefield and York. The whole council of ninety-six members was up for election, with each county electoral division returning one councillor.After the election the composition of the council was;*Labour Party: 61*Conservative Party: 28*Independents: 4*Liberal Party: 3 <S> [    ["1952 West Riding County Council election", "date", "5 April 1952"],    ["1952 West Riding County Council election", "location", "West Riding of Yorkshire"],    ["West Riding of Yorkshire", "excludes", ["Barnsley", "Bradford", "Dewsbury", "Doncaster", "Halifax", "Huddersfield", "Leeds", "Rotherham", "Sheffield", "Wakefield", "York"]],    ["1952 West Riding County Council election", "total council members", 96],    ["1952 West Riding County Council election", "Labour Party members", 61],    ["1952 West Riding County Council election", "Conservative Party members", 28],    ["1952 West Riding County Council election", "Independent members", 4],    ["1952 West Riding County Council election", "Liberal Party members", 3]]
Rajkiya Engineering College, Kannauj, is a government engineering college located in Kannauj, Uttar Pradesh in India. It is a constituent college of Dr. A.P.J. Abdul Kalam Technical University (formerly Uttar Pradesh Technical University) in Lucknow, and had its temporary campus at Harcourt Butler Technical University in Kanpur. It has shifted to its permanent campus in July 2017. The college offers Bachelors programs in electrical engineering, computer science engineering, electronic engineering and civil engineering. Admission in college is done through entrance test (UPSEE) conducted by AKTU, Lucknow. <S> [["Rajkiya Engineering College, Kannauj", "instance of", "Government engineering college"], ["Rajkiya Engineering College, Kannauj", "located in", "Kannauj, Uttar Pradesh, India"], ["Rajkiya Engineering College, Kannauj", "constituent college of", "Dr. A.P.J. Abdul Kalam Technical University"], ["Dr. A.P.J. Abdul Kalam Technical University", "formerly known as", "Uttar Pradesh Technical University"], ["Dr. A.P.J. Abdul Kalam Technical University", "located in", "Lucknow"], ["Rajkiya Engineering College, Kannauj", "temporary campus at", "Harcourt Butler Technical University, Kanpur"], ["Rajkiya Engineering College, Kannauj", "permanent campus at", "July 2017"], ["Rajkiya Engineering College, Kannauj", "offers programs in", "Electrical engineering, Computer science engineering, Electronic engineering, Civil engineering"], ["Admission in college", "done through", "Entrance test (UPSEE) conducted by AKTU, Lucknow"]]
