Lucia Aniello (born 1983) is an Italian-born American director, writer, and producer best known for her work on Comedy Central's "Broad City." She has directed and written episodes of "Broad City", as well as the miniseries "Time Traveling Bong" and the 2017 film, "Rough Night". Aniello resides in Los Angeles with her boyfriend and comedic partner Paul W. Downs, with whom she co-wrote "Rough Night". <S> [["Lucia Aniello", "instance of", "Director"], ["Lucia Aniello", "instance of", "Writer"], ["Lucia Aniello", "instance of", "Producer"], ["Lucia Aniello", "nationality", "Italian-born American"], ["Lucia Aniello", "known for", "Broad City"], ["Lucia Aniello", "residence", "Los Angeles"], ["Lucia Aniello", "partner", "Paul W. Downs"], ["Lucia Aniello", "co-wrote", "Rough Night"], ["Broad City", "created by", "Lucia Aniello"], ["Time Traveling Bong", "created by", "Lucia Aniello"], ["Rough Night", "created by", "Lucia Aniello"]]
