Garrett W. Hagedorn (September 16, 1910 – August 9, 1985) was an American Republican Party politician who served in the New Jersey Senate, where he represented the 40th Legislative District from 1968 until his death.Born and raised in Midland Park, New Jersey, Hagedorn attended the schools of the Eastern Christian School Association, then in Paterson, New Jersey. <S> [["Garrett W. Hagedorn", "date of birth", "September 16, 1910"], ["Garrett W. Hagedorn", "date of death", "August 9, 1985"], ["Garrett W. Hagedorn", "political party", "Republican Party"], ["Garrett W. Hagedorn", "position", "New Jersey Senate"], ["Garrett W. Hagedorn", "district represented", "40th Legislative District"], ["Garrett W. Hagedorn", "place of birth", "Midland Park, New Jersey"], ["Garrett W. Hagedorn", "education", "Eastern Christian School Association"], ["Eastern Christian School Association", "location", "Paterson, New Jersey"]]
Dámaso José Lescaille Tabares (December 11, 1934 – January 27, 2014) was a Cuban revolutionary, journalist, intelligence officer and ambassador. <S> [["Dámaso José Lescaille Tabares", "occupation", "Revolutionary"], ["Dámaso José Lescaille Tabares", "occupation", "Journalist"], ["Dámaso José Lescaille Tabares", "occupation", "Intelligence officer"], ["Dámaso José Lescaille Tabares", "occupation", "Ambassador"], ["Dámaso José Lescaille Tabares", "birth date", "December 11, 1934"], ["Dámaso José Lescaille Tabares", "death date", "January 27, 2014"], ["Dámaso José Lescaille Tabares", "nationality", "Cuban"]]
