The Holmes Correctional Institution is a state prison for men located in Bonifay, Holmes County, Florida, owned and operated by the Florida Department of Corrections. With a mix of security levels including minimum, medium, and close, this facility was opened in 1988 and has a maximum capacity of 1185 prisoners.Holmes correctional officer Col. Greg Malloy was killed in an exchange of gunfire in February 2011 as he assisted in the manhunt for local killer Wade Williams. <S> [["Holmes Correctional Institution", "instance of", "State prison"], ["Holmes Correctional Institution", "location", "Bonifay, Holmes County, Florida"], ["Holmes Correctional Institution", "owner", "Florida Department of Corrections"], ["Holmes Correctional Institution", "security levels", "minimum, medium, close"], ["Holmes Correctional Institution", "opened", "1988"], ["Holmes Correctional Institution", "capacity", "1185 prisoners"], ["Col. Greg Malloy", "occupation", "Correctional officer"], ["Col. Greg Malloy", "killed by", "exchange of gunfire"], ["Col. Greg Malloy", "incident date", "February 2011"], ["Col. Greg Malloy", "assisted in", "manhunt"], ["Wade Williams", "occupation", "Local killer"]]
